Biodiversity is essential to the ecosystem that sustains all life on the planet. Urban parks located in cities across the world provide an opportunity for people to connect to wildlife and nature. Follow CGTN Europe reporter Butchy Davy to one of the most famous city parks in London in the United Kingdom to see the unique biosphere there. About Urban Jungles Series: To mark International Day for Biological Diversity on May 22, CGTN Nature invited experts and reporters from the UK and the U.S. to join a livestream during which guests discussed on how cities, more specifically urban parks, contribute to biodiversity. The series highlights CGTN reporters' vlogs of their tours in different city parks and the wildlife they discovered there. (Cover image a video screenshot) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)